                            <comment id="15339150" author="onurakdemir" created="Mon, 20 Jun 2016 08:24:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;By default DefaultNettyHttpBinding class ignores blank spaces, (allowEmptyValues is false )&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is it the correct way to change allowEmptyValues to true?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15339510" author="jvz" created="Mon, 20 Jun 2016 13:47:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why oh why would it be considered proper behavior to trim data in a low level library like this by default? Magic by default is usually wrong (for example, see how URL decoding is not done by default in rest-dsl).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
